INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'Mythopoeia', 'Blessed are the legend-makers with their rhyme of things not found within recorded time.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'On Fairy-Stories', 'The story-maker proves a successful "sub-creator". He makes a Secondary World which your mind can enter. Inside it, what he relates is "true": it accords with the laws of that world. You therefore believe it, while you are, as it were, inside. The moment disbelief arises, the spell is broken; the magic, or rather art, has failed.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'From an interview with Dennis Gerrolt on the BBC''s radio show "Now Read On" (January 1971)', 'It gives me great pleasure, a good name. I always in writing start with a name. Give me a name and it produces a story, not the other way about normally.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'From a letter to his son Christopher on January 30, 1945', 'A story must be told or there''ll be no story, yet it is the untold stories that are most moving.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'On Fairy-Stories', 'The mind that thought of light, heavy, grey, yellow, still, swift also conceived of magic that would make heavy things light and able to fly, turn grey lead into yellow gold, and the still rock into a swift water. If it could do the one, it could do the other; it inevitably did both. When we can take green from grass, blue from heaven, and red from blood, we have already an enchanter''s power.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'Beowulf: The Monsters and the Critics (1936)', 'The significance of a myth is not easily to be pinned on paper by analytical reasoning. It is at its best when it is presented by a poet who feels rather than makes explicit what his theme portends; who presents it incarnate in the world of history and geography, as our poet has done. Its defender is thus at a disadvantage: unless he is careful, and speaks in parables, he will kill what he is studying by vivisection, and he will be left with a formal or mechanical allegory, and what is more, probably with one that will not work. For myth is alive at once and in all its parts, and dies before it can be dissected.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'Tolkien in Oxford (1968), a BBC 2 television documentary', 'If you really come down to any large story that interests people—holds the attention for a considerable time ... human stories are practically always about one thing, aren''t they? Death. The inevitability of death.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'On Fairy-Stories', 'Fantasy remains a human right: we make in our measure and in our derivative mode, because we are made: and not only made, but made in the image and likeness of a Maker.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'Foreword to the 2nd Edition of "The Lord of the Rings" (1966)', 'The prime motive was the desire of a tale-teller to try his hand at a really long story that would hold the attention of readers, amuse them, delight them, and at times maybe excite them or deeply move them.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'Letter to Stanley Unwin (March 1945)', 'Usually I compose only with great difficulty and endless rewriting.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Treebeard', 'The Two Towers', 'My name is growing all the time, and I''ve lived a very long, long time; so my name is like a story. Real names tell you the story of the things they belong to in my language, in the Old Entish as you might say. It is a lovely language, but it takes a very long time to say anything in it, because we do not say anything in it, unless it is worth taking a long time to say, and to listen to.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkein', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'From the ashes a fire shall be woken, A light from the shadows shall spring...');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Return Of The King', 'I will not say: do not weep; for not all tears are an evil.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'Not all those who wander are lost.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Two Towers', 'For it is easier to shout ''Stop'' than to do it.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'The old that is strong does not wither, Deep roots are not reached by the frost.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'You can fence yourselves in, but you cannot forever fence it out.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'Faithless is he that says farewell when the road darkens.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Two Towers', 'Don''t go where I can''t follow!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Return Of The King', 'Do not spoil the wonder with haste!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'All that is gold does not glitter.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'A box without hinges, key, or lid, yet golden treasure inside is hid.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'Many that live deserve death. And some that die deserve life.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Return Of The King', 'For the time comes of the dominion of men, and the Elder Kindred shall fade or depart.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Return Of The King', 'End? No, the journey doesn''t end here.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'Renewed shall be blade that was broken, The crownless again shall be King.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Return Of The King', 'If this is victory, then our hands are too small to hold it.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 't does not do to leave a live dragon out of your calculations if you live near him.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Return Of The King', 'And so they stood on the walls of the City of Gondor, and a great wind rose and blew, and their hair, raven and golden, streamed out mingling in the air.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'All we have to decide is what to do with the time that is given us.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Two Towers', 'Fair speech may hide a foul heart.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Return Of The King', 'It is useless to meet revenge with revenge; it will heal nothing.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Return Of The King', 'Oft hope is born when all is forlorn.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'Short cuts make long delays.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'And I like less than half of you half as well as you deserve.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Return Of The King', 'Courage will now be your best defense against the storm that is at hand.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'It''s the job that''s never started as takes longest to finish.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Two Towers', 'The wise speak only of what they know.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'If by my life or death I can protect you, I will.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Return Of The King', 'His grief he will not forget; but it will not darken his heart, it will teach him wisdom.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'Faithless is he that says farewell when the road darkens.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Return Of The King', 'And yet their wills did not yield, and they struggled on.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'Advice is a dangerous gift, even from the wise to the wise.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'It is not despair, for despair is only for those who see the end beyond all doubt. We do not.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'Then do not be too eager to deal out death in judgement.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Return Of The King', 'The world is full enough of hurts and mischances without wars to multiply them.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'Courage is found in unlikely places.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'He that breaks a thing to find out what it is has left the path of wisdom.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Return Of The King', 'You will have to be one and whole, for many years. You have so much to enjoy and to be, and to do.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Two Towers', 'Praise from the praiseworthy is beyond all rewards.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'In a hole in the ground there lived a hobbit.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'Escaping goblins to be caught by wolves!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'May the wind under your wings bear you where the sun sails and the moon walks.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'Trolls simply detest the very sight of dwarves (uncooked).');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'If more of us valued food and cheer and song above hoarded gold, it would be a merrier world.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'This is a story of how a Baggins had an adventure and found himself doing and saying things altogether unexpected.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'There is nothing like looking, if you want to find something.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'Out of the frying pan, into the fire.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'Where there''s life there''s hope.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'Is it nice, my precioussss? Is it juicy? Is it scrumptiously crunchable?');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'Even darkness must pass.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'You may not like my burglar, but please don''t damage him.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'Already he was a very different hobbit from the one that had run out without a pocket-handkerchief from Bag End long ago.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'I am fire, I am... Death.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', '''Good morning!'' said Bilbo, and he meant it.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'Only thing to do! On we go!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'Never laugh at live dragons, Bilbo you fool!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'You ought not to be rude to an eagle when you are only the size of a hobbit.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'He thought much, but said little.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'The road goes ever on and on.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'I want to be a healer, and love all things that grow and are not barren.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Return Of The King', '''I wished to be loved by another,'' Éowyn answered. ''But I desire no man''s pity.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Letters Of J.R.R. Tolkien', 'There you will find romance, glory, honour, fidelity, and the true way of all your loves upon earth.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Silmarillion', 'Many are the strange chances of the world, and help oft shall come from the hands of the weak when the wise falter.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'Dreadful as the storm and the lightning! Stronger than the foundations of the earth. All shall love me and despair!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'The world is indeed full of peril, and in it, there are many dark places; but still there is much that is fair, and though in all lands love is now mingled with grief, it grows perhaps the greater.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Silmarillion', 'Love not too well the work of thy hands and the devices of thy heart.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'His love for Frodo rose above all other thoughts, and forgetting his peril he cried aloud: ''I''m coming Mr. Frodo!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'For we put the thought of all that we love into all that we make.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Simarillion', 'All have their worth and each contributes to the worth of the others.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Two Towers', 'I do not love the bright sword for its sharpness, nor the arrow for its swiftness, nor the warrior for his glory. I love only that which they defend.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lost Road And Other Writings', 'I wish life was not so short. Languages take such a time, and so do all the things one wants to know about.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Return Of The King', 'Few other griefs amid the ill chances of this world have more bitterness and shame for a man''s heart than to behold the love of a lady so fair and brave that cannot be returned.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Letters Of J.R.R. Tolkien', 'Out of the darkness of my life, so much frustrated, I put before you the one great thing to love on earth: the Blessed Sacrament.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'You can trust us to stick to you through thick and thin – to the bitter end. And you can trust us to keep any secret of yours – closer than you yourself keep it.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'It is horrible being all alone.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Letters Of J.R.R. Tolkien', 'But the real soulmate is the one you are actually married to.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'I have found that it is the small everyday deed of ordinary folks that keep the darkness at bay. Small acts of kindness and love.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Return Of The King', 'What does your heart tell you?');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Letters Of J.R.R. Tolkien', 'There you will find romance, glory, honor, fidelity, and the true way of all your loves upon earth, and more than that: death, by the divine paradox, that which ends life and demands the surrender of all.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'I don''t know half of you half as well as I should like.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'A hunted man sometimes wearies of distrust and longs for friendship.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Return Of The King', 'On the shores of the sea comes the end of our fellowship in Middle-Earth.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'Maybe the paths that you each shall tread are already laid before your feet, though you do not see them.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Two Towers', 'If the Lady could hear me and give me one wish, I would wish to come back and find you again. Goodbye!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Return Of The King', 'I am glad you are here with me. Here at the end of all things, Sam.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Two Towers', 'Goodbye, master, my dear!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Two Towers', 'There’s some good in this world, Mr. Frodo… and it''s worth fighting for.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Two Towers', 'The treacherous are ever distrustful.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'We are your friends, Frodo.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'Today and tomorrow are yet to be said.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'Don''t adventures ever have an end? I suppose not.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', '-Source Unknown-', 'How do you move on? You move on when your heart finally understands that there is no turning back.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'The chances, the changes are all yours to make.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', '-Source Unknown-', 'A single dream is more powerful than a thousand realities.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'Still round the corner there may wait, a new road or a secret gate.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'The greatest adventure is what lies ahead.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'In these parts... we are plain quiet folk and have no use for adventures.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Children Of Hurin', 'A man that flies from his fear may find that he has only taken a short cut to meet it.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'The mold of your life is in your hands to break.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'The whole thing is quite hopeless, so it''s no good worrying about tomorrow.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Someone else always has to carry on the story.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'There is only one Lord of the Ring, only one who can bend it to his will. And he does not share power.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'For even the very wise cannot see all ends.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Small hands do them because they must, while the eyes of the great are elsewhere.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'If you trust nothing else, trust this. Trust us.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'So comes snow after fire, and even dragons have their endings.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'I will not walk backward in life.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'What weather they shall have is not ours to rule.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Well, you can go on looking forward. There may be many unexpected feasts ahead of you.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'May it be a light to you in dark places, when all other lights go out.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Even the smallest person can change the course of the future.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'There’s no knowing where you might be swept off to.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'It is not our part to master all the tides of the world...');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'No half-heartedness and no worldly fear must turn us aside from following the light unflinchingly.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'It is not the strength of the body, but the strength of the spirit.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'But no living man am I! You look upon a woman.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Deeds will not be less valiant because they are unpraised.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'It’s a dangerous business, Frodo, going out your door.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'I warn you, if you bore me, I shall take my revenge.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'The board is set, the pieces are moving.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'And I come back to you now… at the turn of the tide.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Your time will come.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Do we let them stand alone?');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'And he lives happily ever after.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'There is no curse in Elvish, Entish, or the tongues of Men for this treachery.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'I am Gandalf the White.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Bless you, laddie.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'The Ring has awoken, it’s heard its master''s call.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'I thought up an ending for my book.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'We swears, to serve the master of the Precious.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Let’s face it, Mr. Frodo, we’re lost.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'You will face the same Evil, and you will defeat it.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Mordor. The one place in Middle-Earth we don’t want to see any closer.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'If you are a friend, you speak the password, and the doors will open.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'It''s the one place we’re trying to get to.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'We come to it, at last, the great battle of our time.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'For the time will soon come when Hobbits will shape the fortunes of all.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'The burned hand teaches best.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'I would rather share one lifetime with you than face all the Ages of this world alone.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Go where you must go, and hope!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'It is a lovely language.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'It is a strange fate that we should suffer so much fear and doubt over so small a thing.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', '''Tis most of love they sing indeed.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Who knows? Have patience.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'You are the luckiest, the canniest, and the most reckless man I ever knew.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'It probably won''t come.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Memory is not what the heart desires. That is only a mirror.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Here at last, dear friends.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'But in the end, it''s only a passing thing, this shadow.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Go in peace!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'I don''t think I ought to leave my friends like this.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'After all we have gone through together...');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'But to do what is in us for the succor of those years wherein we are set.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'It is best to love first what you are fitted to love.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'After that advice about fire goes to the heart.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Forgive your Sam.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Torment in the dark was the danger that I feared, and it did not hold me back.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'No onslaught more fierce was ever seen in the savage world...');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'But you cannot trust us to let you face trouble alone, and go off without a word.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Uprooting the evil in the fields that we know, so that those who live after may have clean earth to till.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'It is not the strength of the body, but the strength of the spirit.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'In this Music [the singing of the angels in harmony] the World was begun; for Iluvatar made visible the song of the Ainur, and they beheld it as a light in the darkness.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Arwen', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Your time will come. You will face the same Evil, and you will defeat it.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Sam', 'The Lord Of The Rings', ' Mordor. The one place in Middle-Earth we don''t want to see any closer. And it''s the one place we''re trying to get to. It''s just where we can''t get. Let''s face it, Mr. Frodo, we''re lost.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Frodo', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'I will take the Ring, though I do not know the way.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'There''s some good in this world, Mr. Frodo, and it''s worth fighting for.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'He hated it and loved it, as he hated and loved himself.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Galadriel', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'For the time will soon come when Hobbits will shape the fortunes of all.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Aragorn', 'The Lord Of The Rings', ' If by my life or death I can protect you, I will. You have my sword.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Sam Gamgee', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'I can''t carry it for you, but I can carry you.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Frodo and Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Frodo: I wish it need not have happened in my time. Gandalf: So do I, and so do all who live to see such times. But that is not for them to decide. ');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('The Ring''s Inscription', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'One Ring to rule them all, One Ring to find them, One Ring to bring them all and in the darkness bind them.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Bilbo', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'All that is gold does not glitter, Not all those who wander are lost.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'The Nazgul they were; the Ringwraiths, the Enemy''s most terrible servants; darkness went with them and they cried with the voices of death.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'You have to understand the good in things, to detect the real evil.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'Far, far below the deepest delvings of the dwarves, the world is gnawed by nameless things.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'It may be your task to find the Crack of Doom; but that quest may be for others: I do not know. At any rate you are not ready for that long road yet.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'However it may prove, one must tread the path that need chooses!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gimli', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'Faithless is he that says farewell when the road darkens.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Aragorn', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'Deeds will not be less valiant because they are unpraised.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Aragorn', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'A hunted man sometimes wearies of distrust and longs for friendship.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Bilbo anf Gandalf', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'Bilbo Baggins: No, thank you! We don''t want any more visitors, well-wishers, or distant relations! Gandalf: And what about very old friends? Bilbo Baggins: Gandalf? Gandalf: Bilbo Baggins. Bilbo Baggins: My dear Gandalf! Gandalf: Good to see you, 111 years old! Who would believe it? You haven''t aged a day.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'Much evil must befall a country before it wholly forgets the Elves, if once they dwelt there.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gildor', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'The wide world is all about you: you can fence yourselves in, but you cannot forever fence it out.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'For you do not yet know the strengths of your hearts, and you cannot foresee what each may meet on the road.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Lady Galadriel', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'Even the smallest person can change the course of history.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Faramir', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'In this hour, I do not believe that any darkness will endure.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Galadriel', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'All shall love me and despair. I pass the test.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'It is mine to give to whom I will, like my heart.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'I would have followed you. My brother. My captain. My king.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Sam', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'Where there''s life there''s hope, and need of vittles.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Bilbo', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'Don''t adventures ever have an end? I suppose not. Someone else always has to carry on the story.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Frodo', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'It is useless to meet revenge with revenge: it will heal nothing.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Aragorn', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'His grief he will not forget; but it will not darken his heart, it will teach him wisdom.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Frodo', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'Short cuts make delays, but inns make longer ones.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'From the ashes a fire shall be woken, a light from the shadows shall spring; Renewed shall be blade that was broken; The crownless again shall be king.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'He has passed through the fire and the abyss, and they shall fear him. We will go where he leads.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gimli', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'Memory is not what the heart desires. That is only a mirror.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Galadriel', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'May it be a light to you in dark places, when all other lights go out.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gollum', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'Curse us and crush us, my precious is lost!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'Farewell, Wherever you fare till your eyries receive you at the journey''s end!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Sam Gamgee', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', ' It''s the job that''s never started as takes longest to finish.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Elrond', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'It is perilous to study too deeply the arts of the Enemy, for good or for ill.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Arwen', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'I would rather share one life time with you than face all the Ages of this world alone.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Lady of the Wood', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'The time of the Elves is over. Do we leave Middle-Earth to its fate? Do we let them stand alone?');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Sam', 'The Fellowship Of The Rings', 'I know. It''s all wrong. By rights we shouldn''t even be here. But we are. It''s like in the great stories, Mr. Frodo. The ones that really mattered.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Fly you fools');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'He that breaks a thing to find out what it is has left the path of wisdom.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Generous deeds should not be checked by cold counsel.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Bilbo Baggins! Do not take me for some conjuror of cheap tricks. I am not trying to rob you, I''m trying to help you.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'My time is over: it is no longer my task to set things to rights, nor to help other folk to do so.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Life in the wide world goes on much as it has this past Age, full of its own comings and goings, scarcely aware of the existence of Hobbits, for which I am very thankful.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Well, all good stories deserve embellishment.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'My heart tells me that Gollum has some part to play, for good or ill, before this is over. The pity of Bilbo may rule the fate of many.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Well, here at last, dear friends, on the shores of the Sea comes the end of our fellowship in Middle-earth. Go in peace!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Many that live deserve death. And some that die deserve life. Can you give it to them? Then do not be too eager to deal out death in judgement. For even the very wise cannot see all ends. I have not much hope that Gollum can be cured before he dies, but there is a chance of it.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'I am Gandalf the White. And I come back to you now… at the turn of the tide.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Oh, it''s quite simple. If you are a friend, you speak the password, and the doors will open.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'It is wisdom to recognize necessity, when all other courses have been weighed, though as folly it may appear to those who cling to false hope.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'The burned hand teaches best. After that advice about fire goes to the heart.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'The Ring has awoken, it''s heard its master''s call.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'I did not give you that map and key for you to hold on to the past.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'It is not despair, for despair is only for those who see the end beyond all doubt. We do not.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Be silent! Keep your forked tongue behind your teeth! I have not passed through fire and death to bandy crooked words with a witless worm.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'You cannot pass... I am a servant of the Secret Fire, wielder of the Flame of Anor. The Dark Flame will not avail you, Flame of Udun. Go back to the shadow. You shall not pass.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'He was strong in life. His spirit will find the way to the halls of your fathers.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'A wizard is never late, Frodo Baggins. Nor is he early. He arrives precisely when he means to.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'The board is set, the pieces are moving. We come to it at last, the great battle of our time.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'You can learn all there is to know about their ways in a month, and yet after a hundred years they can still surprise you.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'If in doubt, Meriadoc, always follow your nose.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'There is only one Lord of the Rings. And he does not share power!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'It is a comfort not to be mistaken at all points. Do I not know it only too well!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'All you get to decide is what to do with the time that it is given to you.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Only a small part is played in great deeds by any hero.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Death is just another path, one that we all must take.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'Oh... you would not part an old man from his walking stick?');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', ' Far over the misty mountains cold. To dungeons deep, and caverns old.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Hobbit', 'I am looking for someone to share in an adventure that I am arranging, and it''s very difficult to find anyone.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Hobbit', 'We''ve been blind. And in our blindness, the enemy has returned.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Hobbit', 'You will have to do without pocket-handkerchiefs, and a great many other things, before we reach our journey''s end, Bilbo Baggins.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'Your lullaby would waken a drunken goblin!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Bilbo', 'The Hobbit', ' Frodo, although I must admit I have told you the truth... I might not have told you all of it."');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Hobbit', 'What a lot of things you do use good morning for!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Thorin', 'The Hobbit', 'If more people valued home above gold, this world would be a merrier place.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'Elvish singing is not a thing to miss, in June under the stars, not if you care for such things.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Hobbit', 'You''re not making a very splendid figure as King Under The Mountain, are you?');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Hobbit', 'It''s a dangerous business, walking out one''s front door.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Hobbit', 'True courage is knowing not how to take a life, but when to spare it.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'There is nothing like looking, if you want to find something.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Hobbit', 'The world is not in your books and maps; it''s out there.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Bilbo', 'The Hobbit', 'I don''t want any trouble, you understand? Just show me the way to get out of here, and I''ll be on my way.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Bilbo', 'The Hobbit', 'Thror''s love of gold had grown too fierce. A sickness had begun to grow within him. It was a sickness of the mind. And where sickness thrives bad things will follow.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Thranduil', 'The Hobbit', 'Such is the nature of evil. Out there in the vast ignorance of the world it festers and spreads.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'In a hole in the ground there lived a hobbit.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Thorin', 'The Hobbit', 'Many die in war. Life is cheap. But a treasure such as this cannot be counted in lives lost. It is worth all the blood we can spend.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Hobbit', 'Far to the east, over ranges and rivers lies a single solitary peak.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Hobbit', 'May the wind under your wings bear you where the sun sails and the moon walks.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Hobbit', 'There is a lot more in Bilbo than you guess, and a deal more than he has any idea of himself.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'It was a hobbit hole, and that means comfort.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Thorin', 'The Hobbit', 'Loyalty, honor, a willing heart. I can ask no more than that.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Bilbo', 'The Hobbit', 'Go back?” he thought. “No good at all! Go sideways? Impossible! Go forward? Only thing to do! On we go!” So up he got, and trotted along with his little sword held in front of him and one hand feeling the wall, and his heart all of a patter and a pitter.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Éowyn', 'The Return Of The King', 'And then her heart changed, or at least she understood it; and the winter passed, and the sun shone upon her.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Hamfast Gamgee', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'All''s well that ends better.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Aragorn', 'The Return Of The King', 'His grief he will not forget; but it will not darken his heart, it will teach him wisdom.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Two Towers', 'I was talking aloud to myself. A habit of the old: they choose the wisest person present to speak to.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gollum', 'The Two Towers', 'Hobbits always so polite, yes! O nice hobbits! Smeagol brings them up secret ways that nobody else could find. Tired he is, thirsty he is, yes thirsty; and he guides them and he searches for paths, and they saw sneak, sneak. Very nice friends, O yes my precious, very nice.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Hobbit', 'Deep down here by the dark water lived old Gollum, a small slimy creature. I don’t know where he came from, nor who or what he was. He was Gollum.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gollum', 'The Two Towers', '‘Stew the rabbits!’ squealed Gollum in dismay. ‘Spoil beautiful meat Smeagol saved for you, poor hungry Smeagol!‘');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gollum', 'The Two Towers', 'Misery misery! Hobbits won’t kill us, nice hobbits.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gollum', 'The Hobbit', 'Curse the Baggins! It’s gone! What has it got in its pocketses? Oh we guess, we guess, my precious. He’s found it, yes he must have.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gollum', 'The Two Towers', 'Curse the Baggins! It’s gone! What has it got in its pocketses? Oh we guess, we guess, my precious. He’s found it, yes he must have.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gollum', 'The Return Of The King', '‘Precious, precious, precious!’ Gollum cried. ‘My Precious! O my Precious!’ And with that, even as his eyes were lifted up to gloat on his prize, he stepped too far, toppled, wavered for a moment on the brink, and then with a shriek he fell. Out of the depths came his last wail precious, and he was gone.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('J.R.R. Tolkien', 'The Return Of The King', 'Frodo gave a cry, and there was, fallen upon his knees at the chasm’s edge. But Gollum, dancing like a mad thing, held aloft the ring, a finger still thrust within its circle.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gollum', 'The Two Towers', 'Gollum’s eyes glinted. ‘He doesn’t know what we minds, does he, precious?');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gollum', 'The Two Towers', 'Smeagol promises to Precious, promises faithfully. Never come again, never speak, no never!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gollum', 'The Two Towers', 'Smeagol will swear on the Precious.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Two Towers', 'He is in great fear, not knowing what mighty one may suddenly appear, wielding the Ring, and assailing him with war, seeking to cast him down and take his place. That we should wish to cast him down and have no one in his place is not a thought that occurs to his mind. That we should try to destroy the Ring itself has not yet entered into his darkest dream.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Lord Of The Rings', 'It is a comfort not to be mistaken at all points. Do I not know it only too well!');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', '“What a pity that Bilbo did not stab that vile creature, when he had a chance!” “Pity? It was Pity that stayed his hand. Pity, and Mercy: not to strike without need. And he has been well rewarded, Frodo. Be sure that he took so little hurt from the evil, and escaped in the end, because he began his ownership of the Ring so. With Pity.”');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Fellowship Of THe Ring', 'Let folly be our cloak, a veil before the eyes of the Enemy! For he is very wise, and weighs all things to a nicety in the scales of his malice. But the only measure that he knows is desire, desire for power; and so he judges all hearts. Into his heart the thought will not enter that any will refuse it, that having the Ring we may seek to destroy it. If we seek this, we shall put him out of reckoning.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Return Of The King', 'It is not our part to master all the tides of the world, but to do what is in us for the succour of those years wherein we are set, uprooting the evil in the fields that we know, so that those who live after may have clean earth to till. What weather they shall have is not ours to rule.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Two Towers', 'Then darkness took me, and I strayed out of thought and time, and I wandered far on roads that I will not tell. Naked I was sent back – for a brief time, until my task is done. ');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', '“You cannot pass,” he said. The orcs stood still, and a dead silence fell. “I am a servant of the Secret Fire, wielder of the flame of Anor. You cannot pass. The dark fire will not avail you, flame of Udûn. Go back to the Shadow! You cannot pass.”');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf and Gimli', 'The Two Towers', '“Deep is the abyss that is spanned by Durin’s Bridge, and none has measured it,” said Gimli. “Yet it has a bottom, beyond light and knowledge,” said Gandalf.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'It is not our part here to take thought only for a season, or for a few lives of Men, or for a passing age of the world. We should seek a final end of this menace, even if we do not hope to make one.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Frodo and Gandalf', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', '“You are wise and powerful. Will you not take the Ring?” “No!” cried Gandalf, springing to his feet. “With that power I should have power too great and terrible. And over me the Ring would gain a power still greater and more deadly.” His eyes flashed and his face was lit as by a fire within. “Do not tempt me! For I do not wish to become like the Dark Lord himself. Yet the way of the Ring to my heart is by pity, pity for weakness and the desire of strength to do good. Do not tempt me! I dare not take it, not even to keep it safe, unused. The wish to wield it would be too great for my strength. I shall have such need of it. Great perils lie before me.”');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Return Of The King', 'To me it would not seem that a Steward who faithfully surrenders his charge is diminished in love or in honour.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Return Of The King', '“I am with you at present,” said Gandalf, “but soon I shall not be. I am not coming to the Shire. You must settle its affairs yourselves; that is what you have been trained for. Do you not yet understand? My time is over: it is no longer my task to set things to rights, nor to help folk to do so. And as for you, my dear friends, you will need no help. You are grown up now. Grown indeed very high; among the great you are, and I have no longer any fear at all for any of you.”');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Gandalf', 'The Two Towers', 'The treacherous are ever distrustful.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Frodo', 'The Return Of The King', 'There is no real going back. Though I may come to the Shire, it will not seem the same; for I shall not be the same. I am wounded with knife, sting, and tooth, and a long burden. Where shall I find rest?');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Aragorn', 'The Return Of The King', '‘At last all such things must end,’ he said, ‘but I would have you wait a little while longer: for the end of the deeds that you have shared in has not yet come. A day draws near that I have looked for in all the years of my manhood, and when it comes I would have my friends beside me.‘');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Éowyn', 'The Return Of The King', 'But no living man am I! You look upon a woman. Éowyn I am, Éomund’s daughter. You stand between me and my lord and kin. Begone if you be not deathless! For living or dark undead, I will smite you, if you touch him.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Hamfast Gamgee', 'The Follwoship Of The Ring', 'It’s the job that’s never started as takes longest to finish.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Sam', 'The Return Of The King', 'And you’re with me. And the journey’s finished. But after coming all that way I don’t want to give up yet. It’s not like me, somehow, if you understand.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Samwise Gamgee', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'I thought that Elves were all for moon and stars: but this is more elvish than anything I ever heard tell of. I feel as if I was inside a song, if you take my meaning.');
INSERT INTO quotes(author, source, quote) VALUES('Peregrin Took (Pippin)', 'The Fellowship Of The Ring', 'Sam is an excellent fellow, and would jump down a dragon’s throat to save you, if he did not trip over his own feet.');